  "id": "guide/schematics",
  "title": "@ngrx/schematics",
  "contents": "\n\n\n  <div class=\"github-links\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/schematics/index.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n  </div>\n\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n<h1 id=\"ngrxschematics\">@ngrx/schematics<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/schematics#ngrxschematics\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n<p>Scaffolding library for Angular applications using NgRx libraries.</p>\n<p>Schematics provides Angular CLI commands for generating files when building new NgRx feature areas and expanding existing ones. Built on top of <a href=\"https://blog.angular.io/schematics-an-introduction-dc1dfbc2a2b2\"><code>Schematics</code></a>, this tool integrates with the <a href=\"https://cli.angular.io/\"><code>Angular CLI</code></a>.</p>\n<h2 id=\"installation\">Installation<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/schematics#installation\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>Detailed installation instructions can be found on the <a href=\"guide/schematics/install\">Installation</a> page.</p>\n<h2 id=\"dependencies\">Dependencies<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/schematics#dependencies\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>After installing <code>@ngrx/schematics</code>, install the NgRx dependencies.</p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nnpm install @ngrx/{store,effects,entity,store-devtools} --save\n</code-example>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nyarn add @ngrx/{store,effects,entity,store-devtools}\n</code-example>\n<h2 id=\"initial-state-setup\">Initial State Setup<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/schematics#initial-state-setup\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>Generate the initial state management and register it within the <code>app.module.ts</code></p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nng generate @ngrx/schematics:store <a href=\"api/store/State\" class=\"code-anchor\">State</a> --root --module app.module.ts\n</code-example>\n<div class=\"alert is-important\">\n  The @ngrx/schematics command prefix is only needed when the default collection isn't set.\n</div>\n<h2 id=\"initial-effects-setup\">Initial Effects Setup<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/schematics#initial-effects-setup\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>Generate the root effects and register it within the <code>app.module.ts</code></p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nng generate @ngrx/schematics:<a href=\"api/effects/EffectNotification#effect\" class=\"code-anchor\">effect</a> App --root --module app.module.ts\n</code-example>\n<h2 id=\"default-schematics-collection\">Default Schematics Collection<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/schematics#default-schematics-collection\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>To use <code>@ngrx/schematics</code> as the default collection in your Angular CLI project,\nadd it to your <code>angular.json</code>:</p>\n<code-example language=\"sh\">\nng <a href=\"api/data/DefaultDataServiceFactory#config\" class=\"code-anchor\">config</a> cli.defaultCollection @ngrx/schematics\n</code-example>\n<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/ngrx/platform/tree/master/modules/schematics/collection.json\">collection schema</a> also has aliases to the most common schematics used to generate files.</p>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - docs\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - api/data/DefaultDataServiceFactory#config\n - api/effects/EffectNotification#effect\n - api/store/State\n - guide/schematics#default-schematics-collection\n - guide/schematics#dependencies\n - guide/schematics#initial-effects-setup\n - guide/schematics#initial-state-setup\n - guide/schematics#installation\n - guide/schematics#ngrxschematics\n - guide/schematics/install\n - https://blog.angular.io/schematics-an-introduction-dc1dfbc2a2b2\n - https://cli.angular.io/\n - https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/master/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/schematics/index.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\n - https://github.com/ngrx/platform/tree/master/modules/schematics/collection.json\n-->"
